# Fork of zebra called Quagga exists.

with version stable 0.95a
with role    network
with trait   server
with source  ftp://ftp.zebra.org/pub/zebra/zebra-$VERSION.tar.gz
with info    home http://www.zebra.org/
with info    cite 'zebra manages IPv4 and IPv6 routing protocols.
zebra manages IPv4 and IPv6 routing protocols.
It supports BGP-4 protocol as described in RFC1771
(A Border Gateway Protocol 4) and BGP-4+, RIPv1,
RIPv2, RIPng, OSPFv2 and OSPFv3.
GNU Zebra has a good client interface,
so the user can change configuration dynamically.'
